value: Indon, Aru, Kai, New Guinea, New Guinea
Australia, chiefly in the interior. The extent to which this species is migratory is not known but it has been recorded from the Aru and Kei Islands and from Batjan.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: open woodland dominated by Eucalyptus, esp.stunted mallee communities;River Red Gum or Coolibah;open Acaia woodland (Mulga, Myall, Boree);often in satlbush or bluebush shrubland on sandhills & sandy flats
